# Appwrite SDK & CLI Best Practices

## Client SDK (App)

- Import services from `src/services/appwrite.ts`: `databases`, `functions`, `account`, `storage`, `avatars`, `ID`
- Use `DATABASE_ID` (`platform_db`) and `COLLECTIONS` from that file – never hardcode IDs

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
import { databases, DATABASE_ID, COLLECTIONS } from '../services/appwrite';
import { Query } from 'appwrite';
const docs = await databases.listDocuments(DATABASE_ID, COLLECTIONS.SITES, [Query.equal('user_id', userId)]);
```

## Calling Cloud Functions

- Use `executeFunction` or `executeFunctionWithMeta` from `src/integrations/appwrite/executeFunction`
- Appwrite returns `responseStatusCode` and `responseBody` – the integration parses JSON and throws `AppwriteFunctionError` on HTTP errors

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
import { executeFunction, executeFunctionWithMeta } from '../integrations/appwrite/executeFunction';
const data = await executeFunction<MyResponse>('wp-proxy', undefined, { path: '/?siteId=...', method: 'GET' });
// With meta (status, rawBody, executionStatus):
const { data, statusCode } = await executeFunctionWithMeta('stripe-portal-link', { returnUrl: '...' });
```

## Database Queries

- Use `Query.equal()`, `Query.limit()`, `Query.orderDesc()` from `appwrite`
- **Never use `Query.limit(0)`** – Appwrite rejects it; use `limit(1)` when you only need `total`

```ts
// ❌ BAD
Query.limit(0)  // Appwrite rejects

// ✅ GOOD
[Query.equal('user_id', userId), Query.limit(100)]
```

## Cloud Functions (node-appwrite)

- Appwrite cannot use `_shared` imports – inline helpers in each function: `parsePayload`, `createClient`, `ok`, `fail`
- Use global env vars: `process.env.APPWRITE_ENDPOINT`, `process.env.APPWRITE_PROJECT_ID`, `process.env.APPWRITE_API_KEY` (Appwrite also injects `APPWRITE_FUNCTION_*` variants)
- User ID: `process.env.APPWRITE_FUNCTION_USER_ID` or `req.headers["x-appwrite-user-id"]`
- Parse payload: `req.payload` (string or object) or `req.body` / `req.bodyRaw` depending on Appwrite version
- Return `res.json({ success, ... }, statusCode)`

```js
// ✅ GOOD – inline helpers (no _shared)
function createClient(sdkLib, { endpoint, projectId, apiKey }) {
  const client = new sdkLib.Client().setEndpoint(endpoint).setProject(projectId);
  if (apiKey) client.setKey(apiKey);
  return client;
}
const endpoint = process.env.APPWRITE_ENDPOINT || process.env.APPWRITE_FUNCTION_ENDPOINT;
const projectId = process.env.APPWRITE_PROJECT_ID || process.env.APPWRITE_FUNCTION_PROJECT_ID;
const apiKey = process.env.APPWRITE_API_KEY || process.env.APPWRITE_FUNCTION_API_KEY || process.env.APPWRITE_KEY;
if (!endpoint || !projectId || !apiKey) return res.json({ success: false, message: 'Appwrite config missing' }, 500);
const client = createClient(sdk, { endpoint, projectId, apiKey });
const databases = new sdk.Databases(client);
```

## Error Handling

- Catch `AppwriteException` from `appwrite` for 401, 404, etc.
- Catch `AppwriteFunctionError` for function execution failures (has `statusCode`, `parsedBody`, `rawBody`)

## CLI & Config

- Function definitions live in `appwrite.config.json` – add/update there when creating functions
- Deploy with `appwrite deploy function` or `appwrite push`; config drives deployment
- Set `execute` (users, any, team:admin), `scopes`, and `timeout` in config
